---
// Hero.astro - FedAgent project hero section
---
<section id="hero" class="content-section hero-section">
  <div class="title-wrapper">
    <div class="logo-title-row">
      <img src="/logo.png" alt="FedAgent Logo" class="title-logo" />
      <span class="project-name" id="animated-name">FedAgent</span>
    </div>
    <h1 class="main-subtitle-line">
      <span id="animated-title" class="subtitle-text">Towards Decentralized Agent Reinforcement Learning</span>
    </h1>
    <p class="hero-desc">Train LLM agents collaboratively across decentralized clients, without sharing local data.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="resources-section">
    <div class="resources-buttons">
      <a href="https://github.com/canyuchen/fedagent" class="get-started-btn" target="_blank">
        <i class="fab fa-github"></i>
        <span>Get Started</span>
      </a>
      <a href="/pdf/FedAgent.pdf" class="resource-button" target="_blank">
        <i class="fas fa-file-lines resource-icon"></i>
        <span>Paper (PDF)</span>
      </a>
      <a href="#" class="resource-button">
        <i class="fas fa-archive resource-icon"></i>
        <span>arXiv (coming soon)</span>
      </a>
      <a href="#citation" class="resource-button">
        <i class="fas fa-quote-right resource-icon"></i>
        <span>BibTeX</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="teaser-figure">
    <img
      class="teaser-image"
      src="/figures/fedagent_framework.png"
      alt="The FedAgent framework: federated reinforcement learning of LLM agents across distributed clients, exchanging only model parameters."
    />
  </div>

  <div class="authors-section">
    <div class="authors-list">
      <p class="paper-title">Is Decentralized LLM Agent RL Robust to Heterogeneity? <em>An Asymmetric Tale.</em></p>
      <p class="author-line">
        <a href="https://canyuchen.com/">Canyu Chen<sup class="affiliation-marker">1*</sup></a>,
        <a href="https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=55J-zgwAAAAJ&hl=en">Kangyu Zhu<sup class="affiliation-marker">3*</sup></a>,
        <a href="https://billchan226.github.io/">Zhaorun Chen<sup class="affiliation-marker">4</sup></a>,
        <a href="https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=SbACfYQAAAAJ">Zhanhui Zhou<sup class="affiliation-marker">2</sup></a>,
        <a href="https://shizhediao.github.io/">Shizhe Diao<sup class="affiliation-marker">5</sup></a>,
        <a href="https://2prime.github.io/">Yiping Lu<sup class="affiliation-marker">1</sup></a>,
        <a href="https://litian96.github.io/">Tian Li<sup class="affiliation-marker">4</sup></a>
      </p>
      <p class="author-line">
        <a href="https://limanling.github.io/">Manling Li<sup class="affiliation-marker">1</sup></a>,
        <a href="https://dawnsong.io/">Dawn Song<sup class="affiliation-marker">2</sup></a>
      </p>
      <p class="affiliations">
        <sup class="affiliation-marker">1</sup>Northwestern University,
        <sup class="affiliation-marker">2</sup>University of California, Berkeley,
        <sup class="affiliation-marker">3</sup>Brown University,<br />
        <sup class="affiliation-marker">4</sup>The University of Chicago,
        <sup class="affiliation-marker">5</sup>NVIDIA Research, *Equal contribution
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="abstract" class="content-section">
  <div class="section-container">
    <h2 class="section-title">Abstract</h2>
    <p class="abstract-text">
      Training AI agents powered by Large Language Models (LLMs) typically requires centralized access to
      user data, raising privacy and scalability concerns. We explore <strong>FedAgent</strong>
      (<strong>Federated Agent Reinforcement Learning</strong>), a decentralized reinforcement learning
      paradigm that collaboratively trains LLM agents across distributed clients without sharing local data.
      The central reliability question is: <em>is FedAgent effective under uniform client distribution, and
      more importantly, is it robust to client heterogeneity?</em> For the former, we provide the first
      empirical evidence that FedAgent matches Centralized Agent Training and outperforms Local Agent
      Training. For the latter, we first formalize <strong>Agent Heterogeneity</strong> at two structurally
      distinct levels: <em>task-level</em> (what clients ask the agent to do) and <em>environment-level</em>
      (the dynamics in which the agent acts), anchored on the <strong>Input-Dynamics Asymmetry</strong> of
      task-augmented Markov Decision Processes (MDPs), referring to the architectural fact that tasks enter
      the policy through its input channel, while environments do not. Then, we theoretically establish an
      <strong>Asymmetric Robustness Mechanism</strong>: FedAgent is robust to task-level heterogeneity but
      non-robust to environment-level heterogeneity. We further identify three sufficient conditions under
      which FedAgent recovers robustness despite environment-level heterogeneity, and illustrate four
      possible training-curve patterns. On real-world agent benchmarks WebShop and ALFWorld, we empirically
      verify that FedAgent remains robust under extreme task-level heterogeneities and traces a
      stable-degrade-collapse spectrum under environment-level heterogeneities.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<script>
  // Animate title characters
  function animateChars(el, baseDelay, charDelay) {
    const text = el.textContent || '';
    el.innerHTML = '';
    let i = 0;
    text.split(' ').forEach((word, w, words) => {
      const wordEl = document.createElement('span');
      wordEl.className = 'reveal-word';
      for (const char of word) {
        const span = document.createElement('span');
        span.textContent = char;
        span.className = 'reveal-char';
        span.style.animationDelay = `${baseDelay + i * charDelay}s`;
        wordEl.appendChild(span);
        i++;
      }
      el.appendChild(wordEl);
      if (w < words.length - 1) {
        // breakable space between words; a word never splits across lines
        el.appendChild(document.createTextNode(' '));
        i++;
      }
    });
  }

  document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
    const nameEl = document.getElementById('animated-name');
    const titleEl = document.getElementById('animated-title');
    if (nameEl) {
      animateChars(nameEl, 0, 0.07);
      nameEl.style.opacity = '1';
    }
    if (titleEl) {
      titleEl.style.opacity = '0';
      titleEl.style.transform = 'translateY(10px)';
      titleEl.style.transition = 'opacity 0.6s ease, transform 0.6s ease';
      animateChars(titleEl, 0, 0.04);
      setTimeout(() => {
        titleEl.style.opacity = '1';
        titleEl.style.transform = 'translateY(0)';
      }, 700);
    }
  });
</script>

<style>
  #hero { padding-top: 6.5rem; }
  .title-wrapper { text-align: center; }
  .logo-title-row { display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; gap: 1rem; margin-bottom: 1.4rem; }
  .title-logo { width: 72px; height: 72px; }
  .project-name { font-size: 4.2rem; font-weight: 800; color: #2a2f6c; letter-spacing: -0.02em; line-height: 1; white-space: nowrap; }
  .main-subtitle-line { font-size: 2.8rem; font-weight: 700; color: #333; margin-top: 0.4rem; text-align: center; line-height: 1.25; }
  .hero-desc { margin: 1rem auto 0; max-width: none; font-size: 1.2rem; color: #555; line-height: 1.55; white-space: nowrap; }
  .paper-title { font-size: 1.4rem; font-weight: 700; color: #2a2f6c; line-height: 1.4; margin-bottom: 1.1rem; white-space: nowrap; }
  .paper-title em { font-style: italic; color: inherit; }
  @media (max-width: 980px) { .hero-desc, .paper-title { white-space: normal; } }
  .get-started-btn { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.6rem; background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2a2f6c 0%, #3d4aa0 100%); color: #fff; font-weight: 700; font-size: 1.05rem; padding: 0.85rem 1.8rem; border-radius: 40px; text-decoration: none; box-shadow: 0 4px 15px rgba(42, 47, 108, 0.3); transition: transform 0.2s ease, box-shadow 0.2s ease; }
  .get-started-btn:hover { transform: translateY(-2px); box-shadow: 0 8px 22px rgba(42, 47, 108, 0.4); color: #fff; }
  .get-started-btn i { font-size: 1.2rem; }

  .teaser-figure { margin: 2.2rem auto; text-align: center; max-width: 1000px; }
  .teaser-image { width: 100%; max-width: 710px; border-radius: 12px; box-shadow: 0 8px 30px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.12); animation: fadeInUp 0.8s ease-out 0.3s both; }

  @keyframes fadeInUp { from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(20px); } to { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); } }

  .authors-section { max-width: 920px; margin: 1.8rem auto 0; }
  .authors-list { background: #ffffff; border: 1px solid #e8e8e8; border-radius: 14px; padding: 1.3rem 1.7rem; box-shadow: 0 3px 14px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.06); margin-bottom: 0; }

  #abstract { padding-top: 2rem; }
  .abstract-text { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.8; color: #444; text-align: justify; }
  .abstract-text strong { color: #2a2f6c; }
  .abstract-text em { font-style: italic; color: #333; }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .title-logo { width: 52px; height: 52px; }
    .project-name { font-size: 3rem; }
    .main-subtitle-line { font-size: 1.65rem; }
    .hero-desc { font-size: 1rem; }
    .paper-title { font-size: 1.15rem; }
    .authors-list { padding: 1.1rem 1rem; }
    .teaser-image { border-radius: 8px; }
    .abstract-text { font-size: 0.95rem; text-align: left; }
  }

  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .title-logo { width: 40px; height: 40px; }
    .project-name { font-size: 2.5rem; }
    .main-subtitle-line { font-size: 1.45rem; }
  }
</style>
